%F A006066 An upper bound on this sequence is given by A032765.
%F A006066 For any odd n > 1, if n == 1 (mod 6), a(n) <= (n^2 - (2n + 2))/3; in other odd cases, a(n) <= (n^2 - 2n)/3. For any even n  > 0, if n == 4 (mod 6), a(n) <= (n^2 - (2n + 2))/3, otherwise a(n) <= (n^2 - 2n)/3. - _Sergey Pavlov_, Feb 11 2017
%F A006066 The upper bound for even n can be improved: floor(n(n-7/3)/3), proven by Bartholdi et. al.
%e A006066 a(17) = 85 because the a configuration with 85 exists meeting the upper bound.
